---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Ian Portal, a small personal hub for projects, tools, guides, and study notes."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About"
    title="A small portal with room to grow."
    description="This site is meant to stay light, readable, and useful. It holds the tools I build, the notes I want to keep, and the guide formats that help me think clearly."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-grid">
      <article class="card prose-card">
        <h2>What this site is for</h2>
        <p>
          Ian Portal is not just a blog and not just a tool demo. It is the shared home for practical side projects,
          study notes, compact game guides, and anything else that benefits from being organized instead of lost.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card prose-card">
        <h2>Areas of interest</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Small front-end tools with clear everyday use cases</li>
          <li>Static-site workflows that stay simple to maintain</li>
          <li>Game route notes and short-form guide writing</li>
          <li>Learning notes that are useful later, not just during the first read</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card prose-card">
        <h2>What will live here</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Tools like the Packing List Generator</li>
          <li>Study notes on web development and content systems</li>
          <li>Guides and route memos for games</li>
          <li>Future experiments that deserve a stable landing place</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card prose-card">
        <h2>Current stack</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Astro for static routing and Markdown content collections</li>
          <li>Vanilla client-side JavaScript for focused interactive tools</li>
          <li>GitHub Pages deployment with local content-first workflow</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

